    <body style="background-color: white; padding: 10px;">
        <h1>Move nodes</h1>
        &lt;p&gt;If you want the nodes to be in a different location in the diagram, you can easily move them by doing the following:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Open an asset page.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Click&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traceability &amp;gt; Diagram&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;br /&gt;Wait for the default diagram to render.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If necessary, &lt;a href=&quot;/display/DGC50/Change+view+and+layout+of+a+diagram#Changeviewandlayoutofadiagram-view&quot;&gt;change the view&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=&quot;/display/DGC50/Change+view+and+layout+of+a+diagram#Changeviewandlayoutofadiagram-layout&quot;&gt;layout&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Click a node and hold down your mouse button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Move the node to where you want in the diagram and release the mouse button.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;    &lt;div class=&quot;aui-message hint shadowed information-macro&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;span class=&quot;aui-icon icon-hint&quot;&gt;Icon&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;message-content&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;p&gt;Note that you cannot save the view with these changes. You can, however, print the diagram with these changes.&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    </body>
